HEADWORD: Kirk
<hw>Kirk</hw> <pr>(k⟦etil⟧rk)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Scot.; cf. Icel.
<ets>kirkja</ets>, of Greek origin. See <er>Church</er>.]</ety> <def>A
church or the church, in the various senses of the word; esp., the
Church of Scotland as distinguished from other reformed churches, or
from the Roman Catholic Church.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>
<rj><au>Jamieson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

